From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lusoris <lusoris@pm.me>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 13:17:42 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 17/18] feat(deblock): add vf_pelorus_deblock_vulkan (re-encode
 deblock/dering, Vulkan)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The largest real-world pre-encode corpus is re-transcode of already-compressed
sources, which carry DCT block-edge discontinuities (blocking) the new encoder
wastes bits coding as false residual. This filter applies, at the prior codec's
block grid, a weak [1 2 1] low-pass across each boundary, gated by the
cross-boundary step: a small step is a block-edge artefact (smooth it), a large
step is real structure (preserve it). Luma only; chroma passes through.
Zero-copy in VRAM (FF_VK_REP_FLOAT UNORM, bit-depth-agnostic).

Pure pixel transform — does NOT link libpelorus (deps-only registration). The
reference shader libpelorus/shaders/pelorus_deblock.comp and the inline GLSL are
kept in lockstep.

AVOptions: bsize (DCT grid, default 8), edge (band half-width), thr (artefact
step threshold), str (strength), planes.

ADR: docs/adr/0127-deblock.md
